Detailed Description

Packet switched bearer profile. Use this profile type to define PSD data connections (i.e. context).

PdpPacketFilterPtr PsdDataConnProfile::GetPacketFilter (  UINT8  id  )  const
 

Returns the packet filter identified by id. Valid IDs are values from 1 to 8. If the ID is out of range or no packet filter with id is set, then the empty shared pointer is returned.

DataConnProfileId PsdDataConnProfile::GetPrimaryProfileId (   )  const [inline]
 

Returns the profile ID of the PSD data connection whose primary PDP context shall be used to define a PSD data connection using a secondary PDP context. If this is the invalid profile ID (c_invalid_data_conn_profile_id) then this profile defines a PSD data connection using a primary PDP context.

BOOLEAN PsdDataConnProfile::SetPacketFilter (  const PdpPacketFilterPtr &  filter  ) 
 

Sets the packet filter. The filter itself defines its ID which must be a value from 1 to 8. If a packet filter already exists for a specific ID, then it is simply overridden. If and only if the ID is out of range, then FALSE is returned, otherwise TRUE is returned.

See also:
PdpContext::PacketFilter::GetId()

BOOLEAN PsdDataConnProfile::SetPrimaryProfileId (  DataConnProfileId  profile_id  ) 
 

This method is only used for defining a PSD data connection which shall use a secondary PDP context. It sets the profile ID of the PSD data connection whose PDP context shall be used as primary PDP context. If the primary profile_id provided is not the profile ID of a PSD data connection using a primary PDP context, then FALSE is returned.

BOOLEAN PsdDataConnProfile::UnsetPacketFilter (  UINT8  id  ) 
 

Unsets the packet filter identified by id. Valid IDs are values from 1 to 8. If and only if the ID is out of range, then FALSE is returned, otherwise TRUE is returned.

See also:
PdpContext::PacketFilter::GetId()

BOOLEAN PsdDataConnProfile::UsesSecondaryPdpContext (   )  const [inline]
 

Tells if this PSD data connection profile uses a secondary PDP context. This is determined by checking if a primary profile ID is set. Only PSD data connections using a secondary PDP context define a primary profile ID, since a secondary PDP context needs a primary PDP context on which it is based on.
